============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Nash Equilibrium
Branch:       Game Theory
Formula:      No player benefits from unilateral strategy change
Applications: Economics, AI, political science
Discoverer:   John Nash (1950)

Theorem/Law:  Godel's Incompleteness
Branch:       Logic
Formula:      Every consistent system has unprovable true statements
Applications: AI limits, foundations of math
Discoverer:   Kurt Godel (1931)

Theorem/Law:  Fermat's Last Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      aⁿ + bⁿ ≠ cⁿ for n>2
Applications: Advanced number theory, elliptic curves
Discoverer:   Fermat (conjecture); Wiles (proof) (1637)

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

Concept:      Empiricism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   All knowledge comes from sensory experience; mind is blank slate
Philosopher:  Locke/Hume
Example:      We know fire burns because we felt it, not through pure reason

Concept:      Dialectical Materialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   History driven by material economic forces through thesis-antithesis-synthesis
Philosopher:  Karl Marx/Hegel
Example:      Class struggle between bourgeoisie and proletariat drives history

